defs.name: Compress
defs.docs: Raw in-memory compression stream for blocks of data.

defs.name: Decompress
defs.docs: Raw in-memory decompression stream for blocks of data.

defs.name: None
defs.docs:
A typical parameter for passing to compression/decompression functions,
 this indicates that the underlying stream to decide how much data to
 accumulate before producing output in order to maximize compression.

defs.name: Sync
defs.docs:
All pending output is flushed to the output buffer and the output is
 aligned on a byte boundary so that the decompressor can get all input
 data available so far.

defs.name: Partial
defs.docs:
All pending output is flushed to the output buffer, but the output is
 not aligned to a byte boundary.

defs.name: Full
defs.docs:
All output is flushed as with `Flush::Sync` and the compression state is
 reset so decompression can restart from this point if previous
 compressed data has been damaged or if random access is desired.

defs.name: Finish
defs.docs: Pending input is processed and pending output is flushed.

defs.name: FlushCompress
defs.docs:
Values which indicate the form of flushing to be used when compressing
 in-memory data.

defs.name: None
defs.docs:
A typical parameter for passing to compression/decompression functions,
 this indicates that the underlying stream to decide how much data to
 accumulate before producing output in order to maximize compression.

defs.name: Sync
defs.docs:
All pending output is flushed to the output buffer and the output is
 aligned on a byte boundary so that the decompressor can get all input
 data available so far.

defs.name: Finish
defs.docs: Pending input is processed and pending output is flushed.

defs.name: FlushDecompress
defs.docs:
Values which indicate the form of flushing to be used when
 decompressing in-memory data.

defs.name: DecompressError
defs.docs:
Error returned when a decompression object finds that the input stream of
 bytes was not a valid input stream of bytes.

defs.name: needs_dictionary
defs.docs: Indicates whether decompression failed due to requiring a dictionary.

defs.name: CompressError
defs.docs:
Error returned when a compression object is used incorrectly or otherwise
 generates an error.

defs.name: Ok
defs.docs: Indicates success.

defs.name: BufError
defs.docs:
Indicates that forward progress is not possible due to input or output
 buffers being empty.

defs.name: StreamEnd
defs.docs:
Indicates that all input has been consumed and all output bytes have
 been written. Decompression/compression should not be called again.

defs.name: Status
defs.docs:
Possible status results of compressing some data or successfully
 decompressing a block of data.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new object ready for compressing data that it's given.

defs.name: total_in
defs.docs:
Returns the total number of input bytes which have been processed by

defs.name: total_out
defs.docs:

defs.docs: Quickly resets this compressor without having to reallocate anything.

defs.value: fn (&mut self, input: &[u8], output: &mut [u8], flush: FlushCompress) -> Result<Status, CompressError>
defs.docs:
Compresses the input data into the output, consuming only as much

defs.name: Compression
defs.docs:
When compressing data, the compression level can be specified by a value in
 this enum.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Creates a new description of the compression level with an explicitly
 specified integer.

defs.name: none
defs.docs:
No compression is to be performed, this may actually inflate data
 slightly when encoding.

defs.name: fast
defs.docs: Optimize for the best speed of encoding.

defs.name: best
defs.docs: Optimize for the size of data being encoded.

defs.name: level
defs.docs:
Returns an integer representing the compression level, typically on a
 scale of 0-9
